// CorsPolicyMultiError is an error wrapping multiple validation errors
// returned by CorsPolicy.ValidateAll() if the designated constraints aren't met.
type CorsPolicyMultiError []error

// Error returns a concatenation of all the error messages it wraps.
func ( CorsPolicyMultiError) () string {
	var  []string
	for ,  := range  {
		 = append(, .Error())
	}
	return strings.Join(, "; ")
}

// CorsPolicyValidationError is the validation error returned by
// CorsPolicy.Validate if the designated constraints aren't met.
type CorsPolicyValidationError struct {
	field  string
	reason string
	cause  error
	key    bool
}

// Field function returns field value.
func ( CorsPolicyValidationError) () string { return .field }

// Reason function returns reason value.
func ( CorsPolicyValidationError) () string { return .reason }

// Cause function returns cause value.
func ( CorsPolicyValidationError) () error { return .cause }

// Key function returns key value.
func ( CorsPolicyValidationError) () bool { return .key }

// ErrorName returns error name.
func ( CorsPolicyValidationError) () string { return "CorsPolicyValidationError" }

// Error satisfies the builtin error interface
func ( CorsPolicyValidationError) () string {
	 := ""
	if .cause != nil {
		 = fmt.Sprintf(" | caused by: %v", .cause)
	}

	 := ""
	if .key {
		 = "key for "
	}

	return fmt.Sprintf(
		"invalid %sCorsPolicy.%s: %s%s",
		,
		.field,
		.reason,
		)
}
